  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="o">9</subfield>
    <subfield code="m">It is well-known that there is no power-law decaying tail for integral values of the parameter ŒΩ. This can be easily understood if one remembers that V (x) = l(l + 1)/x2 is simply a centrifugal barrier which corresponds to free (no scattering) propagation of the fields</subfield>
